Date: Mon, 6 Jul 1998 23:39:40 -0400
From: Robert A. LaBudde <ral@lcfltd.com>
Source: ANIMALNET & Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy
<BSE-L@RZ.UNI-KARLSRUHE.DE>

The French Farm Ministry was cited as reporting today that a new case of
mad cow disease has been found in the Loire Valley region in central France
and the herd was destroyed.
It was the seventh case of the bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE, or
mad cow disease) reported in France this year, and the 37th since 1990.
